  "prompt": "Where is a good place to find revision material for AQA As and A level Biology?",
  "response": "Finding comprehensive and reliable revision materials for AQA AS and A-Level Biology is crucial for effective preparation. Here are some excellent resources to consider:\n\n### 1. **Official AQA Resources**\n   - **AQA Website**: Visit the [AQA website](https://www.aqa.org.uk) for past papers, mark schemes, and specifications. These are invaluable for understanding the exam format and the topics covered.\n   - **AQA Textbooks**: Use the official AQA-approved textbooks, which are tailored to the syllabus and often include practice questions and summaries.\n\n### 2. **Revision Guides**\n   - **CGP Books**: CGP produces highly regarded revision guides and workbooks tailored to AQA specifications. Look for titles like \"A-Level Biology for AQA: Year 1 & 2 Student Book\" and their revision guides.\n   - **Oxford AQA Science Revision Guides**: These are also specifically designed for AQA Biology and include clear explanations and practice questions.\n\n### 3. **Online Platforms**\n   - **Physics & Maths Tutor**: This site offers free topic-specific notes, flashcards, and past paper questions for AQA Biology. Visit [Physics & Maths Tutor Biology](https://www.physicsandmathstutor.com/biology-revision/).\n   - **Study Mind**: Provides free AQA Biology revision notes, videos, and practice questions. Check out [Study Mind AQA Biology](https://studymind.co.uk/resource/aqa-a-level-biology/).\n   - **Seneca Learning**: An interactive platform with free courses for AQA Biology. It\u2019s a great way to test your knowledge as you revise. Visit [Seneca Learning](https://senecalearning.com/).\n\n### 4. **YouTube Channels**\n   - **Bozeman Science**: Offers clear, concise video explanations of key Biology topics.\n   - **Miss Estruch Biology**: A channel dedicated to A-Level Biology, with topic-specific videos and exam tips.\n\n### 5. **Flashcards**\n   - **Anki**: Create digital flashcards or download pre-made decks for AQA Biology topics.\n   - **Quizlet**: Search for AQA Biology flashcards made by other students or create your own.\n\n### 6. **Past Papers and Practice Questions**\n   - **ExamSolutions**: Offers worked solutions for AQA Biology past papers. Visit [ExamSolutions](https://www.examsolutions.net/).\n   - **Maths Genie**: Provides past papers and mark schemes for AQA Biology alongside Maths resources.\n\n### 7. **School or College Resources**\n   - Check with your teachers for any additional materials or revision sessions they may offer.\n   - Use school-provided textbooks, notes, and access to educational platforms like Kerboodle.\n\n### 8. **Revision Apps**\n   - **Gojimo**: A revision app with quizzes and practice questions for AQA Biology.\n   - **Brainscape**: Offers flashcard decks for AQA Biology topics.\n\n### 9. **Study Groups and Forums**\n   - Join online forums like **The Student Room** to discuss topics, ask questions, and share resources with peers.\n\nCombining these resources will give you a well-rounded approach to revision. Focus on understanding the core concepts, practicing past papers, and using active recall techniques like flashcards and self-quizzing. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
